items.sentence: If you don't do that, then someone else will.
I know that Tom didn't intentionally do that.
You know I'm not eager to do that, don't you?
You didn't know I wanted to do that, did you?
Why don't you let Tom know you won't do that?
Why don't you let Tom know you can't do that?
Why didn't you tell me Tom wanted to do that?
Why didn't you tell me Tom shouldn't do that?
Why didn't you tell me Tom needed to do that?
What we know is that Tom sometimes does that.
